    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-07-10T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-07-10T11:00:00-05:00" n="254"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d254">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">795.00/7–1050: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Holmes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-07-10T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 10, 1950—5 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 10—12:50 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>184. Eyes only for the Secretary. Re <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss>
                    175 repeated Moscow 12,<note n="1" xml:id="d254fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Infra</hi>.</note> saw Younger instead of Strang<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d254fn2">Sir William Strang, Permanent Under Secretary of
                        State in the British Foreign Office.</note> this afternoon who said that
                    your <pb facs="0365" n="345" xml:id="pg_345"/> comments (Deptel 123)<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d254fn3">Transmitted on July 9 at 7 p. m., <ref target="#pg_340">p.
                            340</ref>.</note> would be incorporated one way or another in a
                    follow-up message being sent to Kelly. This message would also give Kelly green
                    light to go ahead. Hope to be able cable you text this message later today.</p>
                <p>Repeated Moscow 14, eyes only for Ambassador; Department pass Moscow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Holmes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
